  "instructions": [
    "In a large skillet, heat 2 tablespoons of oil over medium-high heat.",
    "Add the ground poppy seeds and cook until lightly golden, about 5 minutes.",
    "Add minced garlic and chopped onion to the skillet, sautéing for another 3-4 minutes or until onions are translucent.",
    "Pour in lemon juice and heavy cream. Stir well to combine all ingredients.",
    "Simmer gently on medium-low heat for about 10-15 minutes, stirring occasionally until sauce thickens slightly, adjusting seasoning with salt if needed.",
    "Serve hot as a snack or side dish with crusty bread."
